        {"step_number": 2, "instruction": "Ask the caller to power the device off fully (not just sleep), wait 30 seconds, and power it back on.", "expected_outcome": "Device boots normally or fails to boot."},
        {"step_number": 3, "instruction": "For peripherals (monitor, keyboard, mouse, dock): reseat all cables on both ends and try a different port if available. For laptops: if a monitor is involved, try the laptop's built-in screen.", "expected_outcome": "Issue resolved by reseating/swapping, or persists."},
